flowchart TD
%% The Detection Phase
    Receive[Receive New Message 'Msg X'\nvia Tor Swarm]
    CheckParent{Local DB:\nDo I have the parent\nprev_id of Msg X?}

    Receive --> CheckParent

%% No Gap Path
    CheckParent -- "Yes (No Gap)" --> SaveMsg[Save Msg X to DB\nRender normally in UI]

%% --- UPDATED: The Non-Blocking Gap Path ---
    CheckParent -- "No (Gap Detected)" --> SaveWarning[Save Msg X to DB\nRender with 'Missing Context' Warning]
    CheckParent -- "No (Gap Detected)" --> SyncQueue[(Add Gap to\nActive Sync Queue)]

%% The Sync Strategy Initialization
    SyncQueue --> InitSync[Init Sync Request:\n'Need ancestors of Msg X']

%% The Sequential Fallback Loop
    InitSync --> SelectPeer[Select Next Available Peer:\n1. Own alternate device\n2. Next highest-uptime peer]

    SelectPeer --> RequestGap[Send Sync Request to Target Peer]

%% Target Peer Processing
    PeerReceives((Target Peer Receives Request))
    RequestGap -. "Over Tor/WebRTC" .-> PeerReceives

    PeerReceives --> PeerQuery[Target Peer queries their DB\nfor requested ancestors]
    PeerQuery --> PeerReply[Target Peer streams available\nmessages backwards]

%% Processing the Reply (Local Node)
    ReceiveSync[Receive Sync Stream]
    PeerReply -. "Over Tor/WebRTC" .-> ReceiveSync

    ReceiveSync --> SaveSync[Save received messages\nto Local DB]

    SaveSync --> CheckGapRemaining{Is the gap\ncompletely closed?}

%% Loop or Pause
    CheckGapRemaining -- "No (Partial/No data)" --> CheckMorePeers{Are there more\nonline peers?}
    CheckMorePeers -- "Yes" --> SelectPeer
    CheckMorePeers -- "No" --> PendingTable[(Add to PENDING_SYNCS\nQueue for offline peers)]

%% Successful Closure
    CheckGapRemaining -- "Yes (Gap Closed)" --> RemoveWarning[Update UI:\nRemove 'Missing Context' warnings\nRender newly synced messages]